Description: Rim and bowl sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery cup-skyphos; thickened lip, offset inside, projecting outwards; wholly glazed; inscription cut on exterior.
Curator's comments: Compare Athens Agora P3905 (Agora xxiii, pl. 27 no. 622).
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (pl. 22.2.1)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1533)
